'''''Rob-B-Hood''''' ({{zh-stp|s=宝贝计划|t=寶貝計劃|p=bǎobèi jìhuà|Cantonese:Bō Bui Wie Gack}}) is a [[2006]] [[action comedy]] film written and directed by [[Benny Chan]], starring [[Jackie Chan]], [[Louis Koo]] and [[Michael Hui]]. The film was produced with a budget of HK$16.8 million and filmed between December 2005 and April 2006. ''Rob-B-Hood'' is notable as the first film in over 30 years, in which Jackie Chan, tired of being typecast as "Mr. Nice Guy", plays a negative character—A burglar and [[problem gambling|compulsive gambler]].<ref name="BC">{{cite web
  | title = Interview with Benny Chan
  | publisher = LoveAsianFilm
  | date = 2006
  | url = http://www.loveasianfilm.com/features/robbhood_feature02.html
  | accessdate = 2007-08-13 }}</ref>

''Rob-B-Hood'' tells the story of a kidnapping gone wrong in Hong Kong; a gang of burglars consisting of Thongs, Octopus and the Landlord kidnap a baby from a wealthy family on behalf of [[triad society|triads]]. With the Landlord arrested, Thongs and Octopus take care of the baby for a short time, developing strong bonds with him. Reluctant to hand the baby over, the two are forced to protect him from the triads who hired them in the first place.

''Rob-B-Hood'' was released in Hong Kong, China and Southeast Asia on [[29 September]], [[2006]] to generally positive reviews.<ref name = RT>{{cite web
| title = Rob-B-Hood at RottenTomatoes
| date = [[2006-09-08]]
| url = http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/rob_b_hood/
| accessdate = 2007-08-24 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web
| title = Collection of reviews of Rob-B-Hood by various papers according to Sina
| publisher = Sina
| date = 2006
| language = Simplified Chinese
| url = http://ent.sina.com.cn/f/m/jackybaby/comments/more.html
| accessdate = 2007-08-28}}</ref> The film topped the Chinese box office in October 2006 and despite not being given a release in most European and North American countries, it grossed over US$20 million worldwide.<ref name = Cbx>{{cite web
| title = 宝贝抢钱9000万《宝贝计划》票房雄踞10月影市 
| work = Nanfang Daily
| publisher = Sina
| date = [[2006-11-10]]
| language = Simplified Chinese
| url = http://ent.sina.com.cn/m/c/2006-11-10/10051321684.html
| accessdate = 2007-08-28 }}</ref><ref name = numbers>{{cite web
