  | accessdate = 2007-08-23 }}</ref> The film is rated [[Hong Kong motion picture rating system#Ratings System|IIA]] in Hong Kong (unsuitable for children), G in Singapore and U in Malaysia.<ref name = SG/><ref name = MY/><ref name = "Twitch">{{cite web
| last = Martin
| first = Peter
| title = Rob-B-Hood Review
| publisher = Twitch
| date = [[2007-01-22]]
| url = http://twitchfilm.net/archives/008799.html
| accessdate = 2007-08-24}}</ref> 

The Japanese title of ''Rob-B-Hood'' is プロジェクトBB (''Purojekuto BB''), literally ''Project BB'', the name initially proposed for the film.<ref name = JP/> In Greece, the film is known as Ασύλληπτοι Απατεώνες (transliteration: ''Asulliptoi Apateones''), meaning ''Inconceivable Frauds''.<ref name = GR/>

===DVD===
The first pressing of the DVD was released in Hong Kong in November 2006 on [[DVD region code|Region 0]]. This has since been discontinued and the subsequent standard and limited edition releases were on Region 3. All Hong Kong versions contain two discs: a movie disc and an extras disc. The movie disc features both the cinematic and uncut versions of the film, along with a commentary track by Benny Chan. The extras disc contains a "behind-the-scenes" video, the [[post-production]] [[press conference]], a collection of deleted scenes and the music video of the [[theme music|theme song]].<ref>{{cite web
  | title = Jackie Chan's Rob-B-Hood DVD now available
  | work = Screen Power
  | date = [[2006-11-02]]
  | url = http://www.screen-power.com/competition.htm
  | accessdate = 2007-08-23 }}</ref> The DVD has now been released in other East Asian countries, including China (Region 6), Japan (Region 2), South Korea, Thailand and Malaysia (Region 3).<ref name = "Twitch"/>

On December 26, 2007, the DVD was also released as a Special 2 Disc Set Edition in the USA, containing more than 40 minutes behind the scenes and making of, with region code 1, produced by the Dragon Dynasty.

The limited edition DVD is housed in a box-file style box and contains various pieces of merchandise including branded [[flip-flop|sandals]] and door signs. An even more limited release of 5000 units was briefly available, and handed out at various film festivals. This edition contained a crystal dummy (pacifier) and 2007 calendar in addition to the merchandise in the other limited edition release.<ref>{{cite news 
  | title = Rob-B-Hood (Extended Cut) (Limited Edition) + Souvenir Set
  | work = Product listing
  | date = [[2007-09-14]]
  | url = http://global.yesasia.com/en/PrdDept.aspx/code-c/section-videos/pid-1004570616/
  | accessdate = 2007-08-23 }}</ref>

==Reception==
[[Image:Project BB Japan.jpg|thumb|150px|Promotional poster of ''Project BB'' in Japan]]
''Rob-B-Hood'' was generally well received by critics. The film received praise at the Venice Film Festival for having a delicate balance between action and drama. Jay Weissberg of [[Variety (magazine)|Variety magazine]] described the film as "a mildly fun ride that banked on Jackie's tried-and-true comic charm in a standard baby kidnapping farce enlivened by just enough action sequences to keep hoary diaper scenes from soiling the playpen".<ref name = "Variety"/> Credit was given to the stunt choreography and the acting partnership of Jackie Chan and Louis Koo, although some reviewers were disappointed about the absence of Sammo Hung.<ref>{{cite web
| last = Lawson
| first = Steve
| title = Rob-B-Hood film review
| date = 2006
| publisher = Official website of Steve Lawson
| url = http://www.steve-lawson.net/13757.html?*session*id*key*=*session*id*val*
| accessdate = 2007-09-01}}</ref> 

The plot of ''Rob-B-Hood'' received mixed reviews: The Chinese newspaper Xiao Xiang Chen Bao found it concise, hilarious and touching,<ref>{{cite web
| title = 《宝贝计划》一场欢笑一把泪
| work = Xiao Xiang Chen Bao
| publisher = Sina
| date = [[2006-09-28]]
| url = http://ent.sina.com.cn/r/m/2006-09-28/07571266589.html
| language = Simplified Chinese
| accessdate = 2007-08-28}}</ref> whereas Jay Weissberg criticised it for being unoriginal, similar to that of ''[[Three Men and a Baby]]''.<ref name = "Variety"/> In addition, Felix Cheong of [[Channel NewsAsia]] found the subplots involving the antagonists' families redundant, detracting from the main story and making the film "tediously long".<ref>{{cite web
| last = Cheong
| first = Felix
| title = Jackie Chan now has a diaper-disaster movie to his name
| publisher = Channel NewsAsia
| date = [[2006-09-29]]
| url = http://www.channelnewsasia.com/stories/moviesreviews/view/233120/1/.html
| accessdate = 2007-08-24 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news
|last = Fonoroff
|first = Paul
|title = Rob-B-Hood review
|date = [[2006-09-28]]
|publisher = South China Morning Post}}</ref> However, Chan was praised for his decision to play a darker character in ''Rob-B-Hood''. Andrew Sun of [[South China Morning Post]] stated that "one of the best things Chan can do for his flagging movie career is to play a heavy—a nasty, scum-of-the-earth antagonist, since you do not always have to play a hero to be a hero." Sun emphasised the need for Chan to show flexibility in his roles, citing a number of actors that have thrived by playing the occasional villain.<ref>{{cite news
| last = Sun
| first = Andrew
| title = Hollywood East
| date = [[2006-10-07]]
| publisher = South China Morning Post}}</ref> 

===Box office===
''Rob-B-Hood'' grossed HK$1.2 million the day it was released in Hong Kong.<ref name=HK/> In China, the film topped the box office during the four day [[National Day of the People's Republic of China|National Day holiday weekend]], grossing ¥8.9 million.<ref>{{cite web
| title = 《宝贝计划》票房飘红 黄金周国产电影成牛市
| work = 金羊网-新快报 
| publisher = Xinhua
| date = [[2006-10-09]]
| url = http://news.xinhuanet.com/ent/2006-10/09/content_5180584.htm
| language = Simplified Chinese
| accessdate = 2007-08-26}}</ref> It went on to top the Chinese box office in October with box office figures exceeding ¥90 million.<ref name = Cbx/> ''Rob-B-Hood'' performed well in [[Southeast Asia]], grossing US$404,000 in Singapore, US$400,000 in Malaysia and US$604,000 in [[Thailand]] during its first four days.<ref>{{cite web
| last = Rothrock
| first = Vicki
| title = "Rob-B-Hood" has $5 million opening session
| publisher = Variety
| date = [[2006-10-04]]
| url = http://www.varietyasiaonline.com/content/view/110/
| accessdate = 2007-08-27 }}</ref> In total, ''Rob-B-Hood'' had a worldwide gross of US$20,434,179 despite not being released in North America and most of Europe.<ref name = numbers/>

